Shorts Creator – Network18 Internship

Problem:
During this internship, I developed a tool called Shorts Creator because creating short video content from long videos manually can be time-consuming for content creators.

Approach:
The system automatically converts long YouTube videos into short clips. It first extracts audio from the video and performs speech-to-text transcription, then analyzes the text to identify important segments of the video and generates short clips from those parts.

Tools:
I implemented this system using Python, with FastAPI for the backend, HTML for the user interface, and the Gemini API for processing and analyzing the video content.

Impact:
This tool helps automate the creation of short-form content from long videos, making the process faster and more efficient for content creators.

